  "Water at the bottom of a lake is saltier and therefore requires a much lower freezing point": "",
  "When water freezes, hydrogen bonds arrange water molecules into an open hexagonal structure that is less dense than liquid water. This causes ice to float on top. The layer of ice insulates the water below, allowing aquatic life to survive.": "",
